Police have rescued three children from suspected kidnappers and child traffickers in Delta State. Spokesman Bright Edafe said on Tuesday in a statement that one of the victims, a 16-year-old girl, was kidnapped in Niger State four years ago and sold to a woman in Asaba. Two other victms, 11 and 12 years old, were also reportedly rescued from the woman, police said. The woman and an accomplice are in custody, it was learnt.